      • calcDistance

        public double calcDistance(double x,
                           double y)
        Calculates the (minimum) distance of a given point to the border of the rectangle. If the point lies within the rectangle, the distance is zero.
        Parameters:
        x - left-right location
        y - up-down location
        Returns:
        distance to border, 0 if inside rectangle or on border

        Parameters:

        y - up-down location
        Returns:
        distance to furthest corner of the rectangle

      • intersects

        public boolean intersects(QuadTree.Rect other)
        Tests if this Rect intersects another Rect. Intersection is either interior or border of rect.
        Parameters:
        other - The rectangle that should be tested for intersection.
        Returns:
        true if this Rect intersects the interior of the other Rect; false otherwise.

      • intersection

        public QuadTree.Rect intersection(QuadTree.Rect r)
        Computes the intersection of this Rect with the specified Rect. Returns a new Rect that represents the intersection of the two rectangles. If the two rectangles do not intersect, the result will be null.
        Parameters:
        r - the specified Rectangle
        Returns:
        the largest Rectangle contained in both the specified Rectangle and in this Rectangle; or if the rectangles do not intersect, an empty rectangle.

      • union

        public QuadTree.Rect union(QuadTree.Rect r)
        Adds a Rect to this Rect. The resulting Rect is the union of the two rectangles (i.e. the minimum rectangle that contains the two original rectangles)
        Parameters:
        r - the specified Rect

      • scale

        public QuadTree.Rect scale(double scaleX,
                           double scaleY)
        Increases the size of the rectangle by scaleX and scaleY. (and "increase by" means: 1.0: increase it by 100% (scale it by 2.0) -0.5: decrease it by 50% (scale it by 0.5) 0.0: do nothing) michaz
